### 1. Create a user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "securepass123",
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "consent": true
}

> {% client.global.set("userId", response.body.id) %}

---

### 2. Create a product
POST http://localhost:3000/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Antique Vase",
  "description": "Rare 18th-century vase",
  "price": 150,
  "pictures": ["https://example.com/vase.jpg"]
}

> {% client.global.set("productId", response.body.id) %}

---

### 3. Create an auction
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auctions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Antique Vase Auction",
  "startingPrice": 150,
  "endsAt": "2025-08-10T18:00:00.000Z",
  "ownerId": "{{userId}}",
  "productId": "{{productId}}"
}

> {% client.global.set("auctionId", response.body.id) %}

---

### 4. Send a bid (simulating Kafka consumer POST)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/kafka/bid
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 175,
  "auctionId": "{{auctionId}}",
  "user": "{{userId}}"
}

